:Purity
1-5,Pure (The new chapter is a direct descendent of its Progenitor.  It is likely to maintain close contact with its Progenitor and many brother Successors, and follows the traditions of its peers closely.)
6-7,A New Generation (Attempts have been made to "breed out" real or perceived flaws in the Gene-Stock, introducing some divergence.  Most likely definte their own traditions and write their own histories, looking forward to the future instead of back to the past.  Their demeanor varies from the Progenitor.)
8-9,Altered Stock (The Gene-Seed has subtly altered, causing some zygotes to become deficient.  They may have links to the Progenitor, but the Chapter might be shunned because they are subtly different to their bretheren.  They have a special Gene-Seed deficiency unlike their Progenitor)
10,Flawed (The Chapter is marked apart from its brother Successors.  They must forge their own destiny, either embracing or raging against their fate.  either earning glory despite the flaw, or are consumed by it, burning brightly, if all too briefly)

:Codex Demeanour
1,Swift as the Wind (excel at rapid strikes and lightning raids.  Quick to anger, quick to jest, impatient but with great personal intiative.  Why wait, when immediate action can take the foe instead of time wasted on protracted planning)
2,Cleanse and Purify (no trace an an enemy should be left behind, burn the corpse, destroy his works, burn down his cities and scour his worlds of life.  They often favor weapons that immolate, incinerate, atomise or blast apart their foe, particularly fond of flamers, meltaguns and plasma guns)
3,No Mercy, No Respite (no concept of the notion of defeat and would rather die.  Stubborn in the face of adveristy, capable of the most awe-inspiring feats of courage.  They might even ignore orders from higher up in the chain of command)
4,Purity Above All (no patience for any hint of genetic deviation, in humanity at large or in other Space Marine Chapoters.  They regard allied Abhumans as monsters and refuse to serve alongside them, even other brother Chapters with unusual genetic traits might be extended to this.  They are unstoppable when fighting the mutant, but it is hard to work with other Chapters as many might be considered impure in some way.)
5,Scion of Mars (have access to the most arcane and revered of weapons, armour and other devices.  May have served side by side with the servants of the Omnissiah in a past campaign, devloping a certain expertise in the use of advanced wargear, they eschew simple weapons, favouring complex ones)
6,See, But Don't be Seen (maintaining a silent, unseen vigil on the foe, striking when target is weakest and most vulnerable.  They approach from the night and shadows, unanticipated quarters before vanishing once more, they are patient and wily cunning considering those who charge headlong to be rash and unsubtle)
7,Suffer Not the Alien to Live (participating in countless xenos-wars, suffered at the hands/claws/tentacles of ravening alien beings, and harbour a special hatred for a particular xenos strain, or indeed all aliens.  Often believe in sancity of human form, and may eschew the use of augmetics unless absolutely needed.  No toleration for any alien species, not even listening, but rather putting a bolter round through the head before it speaks a word, even if faced with total war)
8,Suffer Not the Work of Heretics (crimes against humanity by heretics and schismatics are focused on.  Perhaps they fought a crusade against an enemy like that, and developed a special hatred for those who turn from the light of the Emperor.  They may even see a subtle tain of heresy in other Chapters' traditions)
9,Brothers in Battle (regardless of Chapter or Progenitor, all Space Marines are Brothers.  They may come to look down upon those outside of the Adeptus Astartes, believing (often quite rightly) that none can match their own standards)
10,Uphold the Honour of the Emperor (trust above all things that the Emperor will guide their hands and protect them, and his praises are ever on their lips.  They wish to prove themselves worthy in the eyes of the Emperor, often bombastic and prideful, they make bold, frontal assaults over stealth, so the enemy may know that their doom is come.)